    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You're absolutely right, in fact you can't even access the tab while offline (It just shows the offline view.) There's no reason you shouldn't be able to generate a signed transaction on the contracts tab while offline.\r\n\r\nIt'll probably take a bit of refactoring to get this tab working, so what I'd say is that in the mean time, you'll probably want to:\r\n* Use a bogus private key (not MetaMask) and generate the transaction with the inputs you want\r\n* Copy the `data` field from the raw transaction\r\n* Go offline, unlock the wallet you actually want to send from on the send view\r\n* Enter the address of the contract in question\r\n* Toggle advanced mode (at transaction fee) and paste the data in that you copied from before\r\n* Generate transaction to contract address\r\n* Broadcast signed transaction when online\r\n\r\nThis is definitely not the most fun process, but it should work without having to sign online.",
